node.text: Offering inspiration for @PacSun's Spring '21 Design Competition, which invites designers of all skill levels to create a T-shirt for the retailer, @mikecherman of @chinatownmarket shows us how to design a T-shirt. node.text:
@hypebeastgaming: @heritageauctions is back to offer a super-rare version of The Legend of Zelda for the NES. This special sealed copy is from the game’s very first production run that lasted for a few months in late 1987 and is the earliest known copy of the game in existence at this quality. Pre-bidding has seen the 9.0 WATA graded 1987 NES cartridge surpass $110,000 before the auction’s July 9 start date.⁠
Photo: Heritage Auctions

@hypebeastkicks: Get a closer look at the @nike Dunk Low “SiEMPRE Familia.” Seemingly commemorating Dia de Los Muertos or “the day of the dead,” the shoe is inspired by lizard motifs commonly hand-painted for the Mexican holiday. A dash of vibrance appears on the Swoosh and heel tab, while a full-color lizard graphic is embroidered on the heel. An official release date has yet to be announced but the shoe will likely drop on this year’s Day of the Dead. ⁠⁠
Photo: @repgod888

node.text:
@hypeart: New York-based artist @adamparkersmith is presenting his solo exhibition entitled “Standing on the Moon" at @theholenyc. Best known for his satiric sculptures depicting whimsical subjects, this exhibition will be home to Sarcophagi statues that resemble sub-zero sleeping bags. While they may look soft to touch,  they are crafted using unlikely materials such as resin, steel and urethane. “Standing on the Moon" is on view through August 8. ⁠⁠
Photo: The Hole

@hypebeastwatches: @antiquorum will be the first auction house to offer a green-dialed @patekphilippe Ref. 5711-1A-014 Nautilus. What makes the 2021 timepiece even rarer is that it arrives sealed, even though authorized Patek Philippe dealers were instructed not to supply its watches to customers sealed inside the original plastic factory wrap. Expect it to land on Antiquorum’s auction on July 21 with an estimated value of $60,000 to $120,000 USD.⁠⁠ ⁠
Photo: Antiquorum

#hypeAF: London’s Islington Square is currently playing host to a duo of bold and colorful ping pong tables that are a result of a recent collaboration between design consultancy @campbellhaybranding and creative studio @artof_pingpong. The partnership is comprised of eight uniquely designed tables, two reinforced fiberglass iterations available now for public play, with the remaining six currently on display at The Gallery at Islington Square until later in the year. The exhibition will be open until September 2021.⁠⁠
Photo: The Art of Ping Pong⁠⁠

@hypebeastkicks: @dior is releasing yet another "dad" sneaker dubbed B30 perfect for flexing during the Summer BBQ day. Arriving in 5 colorways, the shoes feature a classic mesh base with leather overlays combined with an embellished large “CD” (Christian Dior) graphic and most but not all of the overlays are trimmed with contrasting lines. Further branding is provided by the bold Dior B30 badge on the tongue, an embossed Dior hit on the midsole and a touch of flair on the heel. These are set to release in October for approximately $1,056 USD.⁠⁠
Photo: Dior

@hypebeaststyle: @archivalreinvent continues to explore the future of functionality, garment construction, and the boundaries of design with its FW21 collection. The technical range is comprised of outerwear, shirts, T-shirts, pants, and shorts that are packable in concealable bags, external pockets, and integrated backpacks. Standouts include the Parka Jacket, 3D Suit Jacket, and Transformable Multi-Pocket Shorts that are constructed of lightweight materials treated with Teflon Fabric Protector. Head to ARCHIVAL REINVENT's website to check out the full lineup.⁠⁠

The new set of League Shorts introduces a fictional rivalry between the "Heat Starters" and "Poison Shadows," drawing from fan-favorite Pokémon, Charizard, and Gengar.
